## Analysis of the Main Target Image

The main target image shows two distinct structures on a dark checkered floor:

1. Left Structure:
   - Red rectangular block with an arch-shaped hole through it (vertically positioned)
   - Two blue cubes positioned in front of the arch opening

2. Right Structure:
   - Three orange cylindrical pillars (vertical orientation)
   - Two yellow rectangular blocks (horizontal orientation) forming a T-shaped top
   - One orange triangular prism cap on the top of the central pillar

### Block Count and Layers:
- Total blocks: 8 blocks (2 red blocks, 2 blue blocks, 2 yellow blocks, 3 orange cylindrical pillars, 1 orange triangular cap)
- Left structure: 3 blocks arranged as 1 red archway with 2 blue cubes in front
- Right structure: 5 blocks with 3 vertical cylinders, topped by 2 yellow rectangles in a T-formation, with a triangular cap on the tallest cylinder

## Block Selection from Dictionary

Based on the main target image, I'll identify the required blocks from the dictionary:

### Left Structure:
- Red archway: Block index 1
- Blue cubes: Block index 3 (used twice)

### Right Structure:
- Orange cylindrical pillars: Block index 8 (used three times)
- Yellow horizontal rectangular blocks: 
  - Longer block (top of T): Block index 7
  - Shorter block (side of T): Block index 5
- Orange triangular cap: Block index 13

## Assembly Order

{
Step1: Move block with index 8 (central vertical orange cylinder)
Step2: Move block with index 8 (right vertical orange cylinder)
Step3: Move block with index 8 (left vertical orange cylinder)
Step4: Move block with index 7 (long yellow rectangular block across top)
Step5: Move block with index 5 (short yellow rectangular block on side)
Step6: Move block with index 13 (orange triangular cap on top)
Step7: Move block with index 1 (red archway)
Step8: Move block with index 3 (first blue cube)
Step9: Move block with index 3 (second blue cube)
}
